OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FThe Russian journalist     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Frefusing to be silenced    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The Russian authorities may have shut  
OL,6, down his newspaper, but journalist     
OL,7, Dmitry Muratov refuses to be silenced. 
OL,9,FWhen we meet in Moscow, the            
OL,10,Feditor-in-chief of Novaya Gazeta and   
OL,11,FRussia's Nobel Peace Prize laureate is 
OL,12,Fworried how far the Kremlin will go in 
OL,13,Fits confrontation with the West.       
OL,15,F"Two generations have lived without the
OL,16,Fthreat of nuclear war," Mr Muratov     
OL,17,Ftells me. "But this period is over.    
OL,18,FWill Putin press the nuclear button, or
OL,19,Fwon't he? Who knows? No one knows this.
OL,20,FThere isn't a single person who can say
OL,21,Ffor sure."                             
